            <div type="translation" resp="part:reda part:emfr">
                
                <p n="1"> 		
                    Prosperity! Fortune!
                </p>
                
                <p n="1-3">
                    This is the sixth year of king Tribhuvana-cakravarti Vīrarājendra.
                </p>
                
                <p n="3-8">
                    I, Vaṇakōvaraiyaṉ, Rājarāja-deva, Lord <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nāyaṉar</foreign></supplied> and feudatory <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>uṭaiya</foreign></supplied> from Āṟakaḷūr situated in Kīḻāṟṟūr, a subdivision <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kūṟṟattu</foreign></supplied> of the Jananātha-vaḷa-nāṭu in Milāṭu, have given as <foreign>devadana</foreign> to Nalla-nāyaṉar, Lord of Nallūr, the village <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ūr āvatu</foreign></supplied> after entering in the register of the temple <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tiruvariyil</foreign></supplied> and engraved on stone.
                </p>
                
                <p n="8-10">
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">That is the village of</supplied> Kaccuvakkuṭi, with its  wet and dry lands, located in Kīḻāṟṟūr, a subdivision kūṟṟattu of the Jananātha-vaḷa-nāṭu in Milāṭu.
                </p>
                
                <p n="10=13">
                    As regards to this village <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ivvūṟ paṭi</foreign></supplied>, whatever lies in the four boundaries included in the <foreign>devadanam</foreign>, the petty taxes <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kiḻiṟai paṭṭam</foreign></supplied>, tank associated <supplied reason="subaudible">taxes</supplied> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>paṉar kuṭṭai</foreign></supplied>, and the village watching tax <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>pāṭikāval</foreign></supplied>, shall not be taken <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>koḷḷa kaṭavatu allātu ākavum</foreign></supplied>.
                </p>
                
                <p n="13-16">
                    In this way <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ippaṭikku</foreign></supplied>, after pouring water on the holy feet of Nalla-nāyaṉar, I, Vāṇakōvaraiyāṉ, alias Makatai Nāṭāḻvāṉ, land-owner from * * *, have given <supplied reason="subaudible">this village</supplied>.
                </p>
                
                <p n="16">
                   This is under the protection of the <foreign>paṉmāheśvaras</foreign>. 
                </p>
                  
